comments:
migrating from eclipse 2 to 3.0M9, i imported some projects to my clean 3.0M9
workspace. after the import, all my projects seemed to have failures (what seams
to be reasonable, as not all class path variables were set in preferences). But
no errors were reported in task view. i tried arround changing the the task view
filters without getting any message in the task view.
after setting all classpath variables and ensuring that all build path libs are
available, the project stays marked faulty and the task view stays empty.

somewhere in the .log file i found the exception below. when i removed the
project mentioned in the exception, the exception itself did not occour again,
but the task view stays empty.
